WEBVTT

00:00:01.899 --> 00:00:05.860
These are challenging times, aren't they?

00:00:05.860 --> 00:00:09.419
Think of the challenges this pandemic has created.

00:00:09.419 --> 00:00:16.260
It has closed down businesses, delayed school openings, postponed sporting events and more,

00:00:16.260 --> 00:00:20.500
but it has not stopped the flow of spiritual food.

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:25.620
Jesus knew long ago that his followers would find themselves in the time of the end, facing

00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:29.460
the most distressing period in human history.

00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:34.579
And he assured them that through a faithful slave, they would receive food at the proper

00:00:34.579 --> 00:00:40.659
time, which would give them hope and strengthen them to endure.

00:00:40.659 --> 00:00:45.380
True, we've had to adjust how we prepare and serve the spiritual food.

00:00:45.380 --> 00:00:50.500
However, we've continued to receive the watch, share, and awake magazines, meeting

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:56.939
workbooks, new original songs and videos, an entire convention program, and even the release

00:00:56.939 --> 00:01:01.619
of the New World translation in more languages.

00:01:01.619 --> 00:01:09.180
This is exactly what Jehovah promised he would provide, as stated at Isaiah 65 and verse

00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:10.180
13.

00:01:10.180 --> 00:01:14.980
Therefore, this is what the sovereign Lord Jehovah says.

00:01:14.980 --> 00:01:20.500
Look, my servants will eat, but you will go hungry.

00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:26.299
Look, my servants will drink, but you will go thirsty.

00:01:26.299 --> 00:01:33.540
Look, my servants will rejoice, but you will suffer shame.

00:01:33.540 --> 00:01:38.060
Those words aren't just a reassurance, they're a promise.

00:01:38.060 --> 00:01:42.980
Despite all the chaos in the world around us, we will have the spiritual food that we need

00:01:42.980 --> 00:01:45.459
to stay strong.

00:01:45.459 --> 00:01:51.459
So you might wonder, what adjustments has the governing body made to provide spiritual

00:01:51.459 --> 00:01:56.219
food at the proper time, despite the pandemic?

00:01:56.219 --> 00:02:00.180
How have we seen Jehovah's blessing on these adjustments?

00:02:00.180 --> 00:02:07.180
And on a personal level, what can each one of us do to show our appreciation for these

00:02:07.180 --> 00:02:10.530
provisions?

00:02:10.530 --> 00:02:15.289
Restrictions and lockdowns haven't stopped the work of writing and publishing spiritually

00:02:15.289 --> 00:02:17.650
upbuilding food.

00:02:17.650 --> 00:02:22.610
One example of this is the recent update to the study edition of the New World Translation

00:02:22.610 --> 00:02:25.770
of the Holy Scriptures.

00:02:25.770 --> 00:02:33.330
Ideas and Ephesians are now available in English, with over 340 new study notes, a video,

00:02:33.330 --> 00:02:38.370
media gallery items, and new articles in the appendix.

00:02:38.370 --> 00:02:42.310
Now how about JW.org website?

00:02:42.310 --> 00:02:46.169
The brothers have been hard at work there too.

00:02:46.169 --> 00:02:50.969
Articles such as, what does the Bible say about pandemics?

00:02:50.969 --> 00:02:55.729
And how to deal with isolation have been added?

00:02:55.729 --> 00:03:01.889
Historical is about distance learning, domestic abuse, and alcohol consumption have also been

00:03:01.889 --> 00:03:03.090
added.

00:03:03.090 --> 00:03:08.689
The very issues that are on many people's minds right now.

00:03:08.689 --> 00:03:14.449
How has the pandemic affected the production of our various video projects?

00:03:14.449 --> 00:03:20.250
As you can imagine, with Bethel facilities on lockdown and with physical distancing measures

00:03:20.250 --> 00:03:26.370
in place, we've had to rethink how videos can be safely produced.

00:03:26.370 --> 00:03:31.650
In the following video report, Brother Bob Batco, a member of the Central America Branch

00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:39.020
Committee, explains adjustments the regional video team has made.

00:03:39.020 --> 00:03:42.939
To keep the cameras rolling, the regional video team hosted here at the branch had

00:03:42.939 --> 00:03:46.340
to overcome some pretty big challenges.

00:03:46.340 --> 00:03:48.580
One of them was casting.

00:03:48.580 --> 00:03:54.199
We couldn't invite local brothers and sisters to come in to play roles, nor could the

00:03:54.199 --> 00:03:58.099
Bethel team go out to shoot on location.

00:03:58.099 --> 00:04:04.060
So what did it require, adapting to the local circumstances?

00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:09.460
That meant shooting on Bethel property with Bethel personnel.

00:04:09.460 --> 00:04:16.620
Now that may seem limiting, but they found solutions, the green screen.

00:04:16.620 --> 00:04:25.600
That meant that they could shoot in studio and the actor could virtually be anywhere.

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:30.639
When working on a set here, rigorous safety precautions need to be taken.

00:04:30.639 --> 00:04:35.000
Casting crew members get their temperature checked at the beginning, and the end of each

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:41.120
day, and everyone, everyone wears face masks, including the actors, unless they're being

00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:43.120
filmed.

00:04:43.120 --> 00:04:49.360
The actors maintain physical distancing, win with anyone other than their mate or roommate.

00:04:49.360 --> 00:04:55.560
To minimize contact with a hair and makeup team, they've taken advantage of video conferencing.

00:04:55.560 --> 00:05:01.779
So they would teach the wives how to put beards on their husbands in their Bethel rooms.

00:05:01.779 --> 00:05:07.519
This way only touch ups need to be done on set, and even then, personal protective equipment

00:05:07.519 --> 00:05:09.120
is used.

00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:13.920
And everything is disinfected before and after each session.

00:05:13.920 --> 00:05:19.279
In doing all of this, there was a wonderful spirit of unity.

00:05:19.279 --> 00:05:24.959
During the lockdown, no commuters have been able to come in, so many from other Bethel

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:29.279
departments have been made available to help with the work.

00:05:29.279 --> 00:05:36.040
Some are helping on the production team, others by sewing wardrobes, building sets, and

00:05:36.040 --> 00:05:40.800
nobody went hungry, all the meals were provided.

00:05:40.800 --> 00:05:47.000
In all of this, it's obvious that Jehovah bless not just these arrangements, but also

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:54.399
the governing body, so that they could provide the much needed spiritual food right on time.

00:05:57.680 --> 00:06:03.920
As you can see, we've had to adjust many aspects of video production, and we're grateful

00:06:03.920 --> 00:06:06.839
for the hard work of all involved.

00:06:06.839 --> 00:06:12.480
In fact, all of our video teams, including the ones at World Headquarters, are taking

00:06:12.480 --> 00:06:18.680
similar steps to keep production going while remaining safe.

00:06:18.680 --> 00:06:21.120
But do you see the point?

00:06:21.120 --> 00:06:26.879
The menu of spiritual food prepared well before the pandemic will be presented just as

00:06:26.879 --> 00:06:28.800
planned.

00:06:28.800 --> 00:06:34.720
You might say we've had to adjust some of the kitchen utensils and cooking methods, but

00:06:34.720 --> 00:06:43.120
the meal itself is unchanged and just as nourishing, so you won't miss a thing.

00:06:43.120 --> 00:06:48.800
Another vital part of the process in providing spiritual food to Jehovah's people worldwide

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:54.199
is translation, and that hasn't stopped either.

00:06:54.199 --> 00:07:00.000
Animation teams have been able to continue their work by video conference, and the results

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:02.480
have been thrilling.

00:07:02.480 --> 00:07:08.920
For example, since the start of the pandemic, the new world translation has been released

00:07:08.920 --> 00:07:15.399
in whole or in part in 19 languages.

00:07:15.399 --> 00:07:20.399
Some of these releases had been planned in conjunction with regional conventions that

00:07:20.399 --> 00:07:23.360
were to be held later this year.

00:07:23.360 --> 00:07:30.279
So when the decision was made to present a global convention program by video, the teaching

00:07:30.279 --> 00:07:37.199
committee asks if these newly translated Bibles could be released before the convention began

00:07:37.199 --> 00:07:39.279
in July.

00:07:39.279 --> 00:07:45.879
That way, translators could use the new Bibles when translating the convention program,

00:07:45.879 --> 00:07:53.079
and publishers could follow along with all six sessions using their newly released Bibles.

00:07:53.079 --> 00:08:01.360
Well, through a tremendous effort and with Jehovah's blessing, 13 Bibles were released

00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:08.199
